        "Source": "ANSA"
      }
    ],
    "Description": "Package updates are available for Anolis 8 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\n\nCVE-2021-3621:\nA flaw was found in SSSD, where the sssctl command was vulnerable to shell command injection via the logs-fetch and cache-expire subcommands. This flaw allows an attacker to trick the root user into running a specially crafted sssctl command, such as via sudo, to gain root access. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to confidentiality, integrity, as well as system availability.",
    "Advisory": {
      "Severity": "Important",
